About the Data Set- Heart disease¶

The dataset used in this assignment is the heart disease dataset available in heart-c.csv from the Blackboard. This dataset describes 13 risk factors for heart disease. The attribute num represents the (binary) class attribute: class <50 means no disease; class >50_1 indicates increased level of heart disease.

Data Dictionary: age = age in years sex = sex (1 = male; 0 = female) cp = cp: chest pain type
Value 1: typical angina
Value 2: atypical angina
Value 3: non-anginal pain
Value 4: asymptomatic trestbps = resting blood pressure (in mm Hg on admission to the hospital) chol = serum cholestoral in mg/dl fbs = (fasting blood sugar > 120 mg/dl) (1 = true; 0 = false) restecg = resting electrocardiographic results : Value 0: normal
Value 1: having ST-T wave abnormality (T wave inversions and/or ST elevation or depression of > 0.05 mV)
Value 2: showing probable or definite left ventricular hypertrophy by Estes' criteria thalach = maximum heart rate achieved exang = exercise induced angina (1 = yes; 0 = no) oldpeak = ST depression induced by exercise relative to rest slope = the slope of the peak exercise ST segment : Value 1: upsloping
Value 2: flat
Value 3: downsloping ca = number of major vessels (0-3) colored by flourosopy thal = 3 = normal; 6 = fixed defect; 7 = reversable defect num = diagnosis of heart disease (angiographic disease status) : Value 0: < 50% no disease
Value 1: > 50% increased level of heart disease

Some More Pre-Processing¶

In [5]:
#Changing the data frame into numeric 
#Sex
df<- df %>% 
  mutate (sex=if_else(sex=="male",1,2))
#exang
df<- df %>% 
  mutate(exang=if_else(exang=="no",1,2))
#fbs
df<- df %>% 
  mutate(fbs=if_else(fbs=="TRUE",1,2))

#slope
df <- df %>% 
  mutate(slope =if_else(slope=="down",1,if_else(slope=="flat",2,3)))

#cp  
df <- df %>% 
  mutate(cp =if_else(cp=="typ_angina",1,
            if_else(cp=="asympt",2,
            if_else(cp=="non_anginal",3,4))))
#restecg 

df <- df %>% 
  mutate(restecg = if_else(restecg =="left_vent_hyper",1,
                   if_else(restecg == "normal",2,3)))
#thal 

df<-df %>% 
  mutate(thal= if_else(thal=="fixed_defect",1,
               if_else(thal == "normal",2,3)))
